==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pretorium
<hw>Pre*to"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praetorium</ets>, fr. <ets>praetor</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The general's tent in a Roman camp; hence, a council of war,
because held in the general's tent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The official residence of a governor of a province;
hence, a place; a splendid country seat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pretorship</ent>⟦br⟧
